  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers use packages to start or expand their colonies, considering them a preferred method for beginners due to their ease of handling and availability."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;FLORIDA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Florida produces package bees, making it a primary source for beekeepers looking to obtain packages in the spring."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;GEORGIA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Georgia produces package bees, contributing to the supply of bees for beekeepers in the region."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;ALABAMA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Alabama produces package bees, supporting the needs of beekeepers in the southern states."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;MISSISSIPPI&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mississippi produces package bees, providing a source of bees for beekeepers in the area."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;LOUISIANA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Louisiana produces package bees, contributing to the supply of bees for beekeepers in the southern states."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;CALIFORNIA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"California produces package bees, providing a source of bees for beekeepers in the southern states."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages are used in beekeeping to start or expand colonies, especially by beginners, due to their ease of handling and availability."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;MITE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package bees have been carriers of mites since the mites' incursion into the country, posing a risk to the health of the colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;NUCLEUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both packages and nuclei are methods used by beekeepers to start new colonies, though packages are more commonly used by beginners."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;SPRING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages are available for shipment in the spring, making it the optimal time to start new colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;MAIL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages can be shipped via mail from southern states to other parts of the country."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;TRUCKING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages can also be shipped via trucking from southern states to other parts of the country."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;NORTHERN STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages are not available in time for successful colony establishment in northern states."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages are used to start new colonies, which are groups of bees managed by beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE&quot;" target="&quot;MITES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Packages can carry mites, which pose a risk to the health of the colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A beekeeper installs a package in a new hive and needs to act appropriately, indicating a direct relationship."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8d4fa5f5a2057fb38701d211cf3bf314</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers manage and care for the colony, ensuring their health and well-being."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3bff3799a6338bd2be390d642031fc2e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;" target="&quot;PEOPLE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers are part of the broader category of people who interact with bees, though bees do not recognize individual people."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3bff3799a6338bd2be390d642031fc2e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS&quot;" target="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Nuclei are also used to start new colonies, which are groups of bees managed by beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NUCLEUS&quot;" target="&quot;MITES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Like packages, nuclei can also be affected by mites, posing a risk to the health of the colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1712e3ce0cba3a251f3d6d78a8d75839</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;SMOKE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colonies exhibit specific behaviors in response to smoke, such as engorgement and reduced defensiveness."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1e6e41906583e9d3c61d1d0a4b6f13fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;SKUNK&quot;">
  <data key="d4">22.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colonies can learn to respond to threats like skunks."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Skunks can cause increased defensiveness in colonies through constant harassment."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1e6e41906583e9d3c61d1d0a4b6f13fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;SHADE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">19.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colonies can learn to respond to environmental conditions like excessive shade."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Excessive shade can lower the threshold of defensiveness in colonies."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1e6e41906583e9d3c61d1d0a4b6f13fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;ANTHROPOMORPHISM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Anthropomorphism is used to interpret and discuss the behavior of honey bee colonies, attributing human-like traits to them."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1e6e41906583e9d3c61d1d0a4b6f13fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;DEFENSIVENESS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colonies have a threshold of defensiveness that can be influenced by external factors such as skunks and shade."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1e6e41906583e9d3c61d1d0a4b6f13fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;ENGORGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">23.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colonies engage in engorgement with honey in response to smoke, which is a learned behavior."|&lt;SEP&gt;"Colonies engage in engorgement with honey, a learned behavior influenced by their intelligence."|</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1e6e41906583e9d3c61d1d0a4b6f13fe</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MITES&quot;" target="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">24.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mites are a potential problem that requires precautions, which could be relevant to the use of package bees."|&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;"Package bees can carry mites, which can spread to new hives, posing a risk to bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8d4fa5f5a2057fb38701d211cf3bf314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MITES&quot;" target="&quot;BEGINNER BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beginner beekeepers must take precautions against mites when using package bees, as mites can affect the health of their new colonies."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MITES&quot;" target="&quot;PAGES 148-158&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pages 148-158 contain more information on mites, indicating a source of information."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-8d4fa5f5a2057fb38701d211cf3bf314</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;BEGINNER BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package bees are preferred by beginner beekeepers due to their ease of handling and availability."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;PAGES 148-158&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pages 148-158 provide information on managing mites, which is crucial for beginner beekeepers using package bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;DEFENSIVE BEHAVIOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package bees are less defensive than established colonies, making them easier to handle initially."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;DISEASE TRANSMISSION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package bees minimize the risk of disease transmission due to the absence of comb, but precautions are still necessary."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;TIME&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Using package bees is a slower method of starting a new colony, as it takes time for the bee population to grow and the bees to gain confidence."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PACKAGE BEES&quot;" target="&quot;ORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Package bees lack a home to defend and organizational structure, making them easier to handle but also less prepared for defense."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1a032fe5f052f01f07fcd8734955c8a1</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
