</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNX&quot;" target="&quot;TONGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"An elevated, rigid larynx can make both the tongue and jaw suffer, demonstrating the interconnected nature of these articulators."&lt;SEP&gt;"The larynx's position can influence the tongue's movement, especially when there is tension in the jaw muscles, creating a chain reaction of tension."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5475d765cb82765b1a8119b08e5698f9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNX&quot;" target="&quot;JAW MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Tight jaw muscles can cause larynx tension, affecting the overall vocal performance and creating a chain reaction of tension throughout the articulators."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5475d765cb82765b1a8119b08e5698f9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNX&quot;" target="&quot;HYOID BONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hyoid bone connects the larynx, tongue, and jaw, facilitating their interconnection and affecting vocal performance."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5475d765cb82765b1a8119b08e5698f9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LARYNX&quot;" target="&quot;THIRTEEN MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The larynx is influenced by multiple muscles, including those in the tongue, throat, and palate, highlighting the complexity of vocal control."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5475d765cb82765b1a8119b08e5698f9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
