  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hyoid apparatus, including the hyoid bone and surrounding muscles, connects the larynx, tongue, and jaw, facilitating their coordinated movement during singing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5475d765cb82765b1a8119b08e5698f9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SINGING&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The vocal folds vibrate to produce sound during singing, which is influenced by the position of the larynx and other articulators."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5475d765cb82765b1a8119b08e5698f9</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SINGING&quot;" target="&quot;AIR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Air is essential for producing sound during singing, passing through the vocal folds and affecting the position of the larynx and other articulators."</data>
