</edge>
<edge source="&quot;JACOB&quot;" target="&quot;NEGATIVE REGULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Jacob collaborated with Monod to understand and describe negative regulation mechanisms in detail."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4eeff2956121f6bd69a6ab83659363d8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INDUCER&quot;" target="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The inducer is thought to inhibit a negative regulator (repressor) of enzyme synthesis, changing the initial understanding of its function."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0d1852fcdaa63557848de7e718d223a6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;CONSTITUTIVE MUTANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Constitutive Mutants lack a repressor, leading to continuous enzyme synthesis without an inducer."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0d1852fcdaa63557848de7e718d223a6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;REPRESSOR&quot;" target="&quot;VIRUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Repressor is a protein that keeps the viral genes repressed until activated by ultraviolet light."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-494c656afa2fa45b32cf5c52326889ec</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MUTANT COPY OF THE REPRESSOR GENE&quot;" target="&quot;GOOD COPY OF THE REPRESSOR GENE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Mutant Copy of the Repressor Gene is overridden by the Good Copy of the Repressor Gene, affecting enzyme production."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-0d1852fcdaa63557848de7e718d223a6</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
