  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hidden viruses can be activated by ultraviolet light, leading to their genes being turned on."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-494c656afa2fa45b32cf5c52326889ec</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CELLULAR REACTIONS&quot;" target="&quot;CONDITIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Cellular reactions depend on the current conditions within the cell."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-494c656afa2fa45b32cf5c52326889ec</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;AMINO ACIDS&quot;" target="&quot;BIOCHEMISTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Biochemists study the synthesis of amino acids and the pathways involved, contributing to our understanding of protein biosynthesis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4eeff2956121f6bd69a6ab83659363d8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INTERMEDIATE REACTION PRODUCTS&quot;" target="&quot;PATHWAY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Intermediate Reaction Products are part of the Pathway that transforms a Chemical Precursor into an Amino Acid through a series of enzymatic reactions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4eeff2956121f6bd69a6ab83659363d8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHEMICAL PRECURSOR (P)&quot;" target="&quot;PATHWAY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Chemical Precursor (P) is the starting material in the Pathway that is modified into an Amino Acid through a series of enzymatic reactions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4eeff2956121f6bd69a6ab83659363d8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PATHWAY&quot;" target="&quot;FEEDBACK MECHANISM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pathway includes a Feedback Mechanism where the presence of an Amino Acid inhibits the production of the enzyme responsible for its synthesis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4eeff2956121f6bd69a6ab83659363d8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FEEDBACK MECHANISM&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIFIC AMINO ACID&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"When a Specific Amino Acid is provided, the Feedback Mechanism rapidly shuts off the synthesis of that particular amino acid."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4eeff2956121f6bd69a6ab83659363d8</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
